===Verb===
{{en-verb|buys|buying|bought|past_ptc2=boughten|past_ptc2_qual=rare, dialectal}}

# {{lb|en|transitive|ditransitive}} To [[obtain]] (something) in [[exchange]] for money or goods.
#: {{ux|en|I'm going to '''buy''' my father something nice for his birthday.}}
#* '''1793''', {{w|Benjamin Franklin}}, ''{{w|The Autobiography of Benjamin Franklin|Autobiography}}''
#*: '''Buy''' what thou hast no need of, and ere long thou wilt sell thy necessaries.
# {{lb|en|transitive|ditransitive}} To obtain, especially by some sacrifice.
#: {{ux|en|I've '''bought''' material comfort by foregoing my dreams.}}
#: {{ux|en|You just '''bought''' yourself an assault charge!}}
#*{{RQ:KJV|Proverbs|23|23||'''Buy''' the truth and sell it not; also wisdom, and instruction, and understanding.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|archaic}} To [[suffer]] [[consequences]] for (something) through being [[deprive]]d of something; to [[pay]] for (something one has done).
#* {{RQ:Jack Straw|I|15|VVhat villaine, doſt ſtrike me? I ſweare by the rood,<br>As I am ''Iacke Strawe'', thou ſhalt '''buy''' it with thy blood.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[bribe]].
#: {{ux|en|He tried to '''buy''' me with gifts, but I wouldn't give up my beliefs.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To be equivalent to in value.
#: {{ux|en|The dollar doesn't '''buy''' as much as it used to.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|informal}} to [[accept]] as true; to [[believe]]
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2020|author=[[w:Akwaeke Emezi|Akwaeke Emezi]]|title=The Death of Vivek Oji|publisher=Faber & Faber Ltd|page=201|passage=People like to say that dead people look asleep, and maybe she would have '''bought''' that under different circumstances.}}
#: {{ux|en|I'm not going to '''buy''' your stupid excuses anymore!}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To make a purchase or purchases, to [[treat]] (for a drink, meal or gift)
#: {{ux|en|She '''buys''' for Federated.}}
#: {{ux|en|Let's go out for dinner. I'm '''buying'''.}}
# {{lb|en|poker slang|transitive}} To make a [[bluff]], usually a large one.
#: {{ux|en|Smith tried to '''buy''' the pot on the river with a huge bluff}}

